UYO – The Peoples Democratic Party on Wednesday had course to rejoice following the return of one of its founding members, Chief Inibehe Okorie, after some years of sojourning in the All Progressives Congress. Okorie, who announced his return to the State Working Committee of PDP, led by its chairman, Mr. Aniekan Akpan, said he was returning to add value to the party in the state. “I am delighted to come before you having returned to the PDP, I have done the right thing by returning to the PDP. I want to commend all of you for the wonderful work you have been doing in the party, because if you people have not handled the party well, i wouldn’t have come in. “I don’t know how you have organised the party, but I want to give credit to the Governor, Udom Emmanuel, for putting in place, a very hard-working SWC, headed by brother, Mr. Aniekan Akpan. I have great honour and dignity for this SWC. I am back to bring to bear the little i can offer for the success of the party in the state” While commending the unity and cohesion within the PDP family, Okorie noted that such values would place the party in good stead to win the upcoming polls across all competitions in the state. The business tycoon commended Governor Udom Emmanuel for uniting the party and building effective structures from the wards, chapters to the state level and pledged to join hand in the rebuilding process.